Replace every `runtimeRegistry.getDefault()` call in `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts` with `runtimeRegistry.resolveForSession(sessionId)`. Session creation becomes the single place where a new session's runtime is chosen (from explicit hint > agent manifest > server default) and persisted before the first stream event.

**Target files:**
- `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`
- `apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/sessions.test.ts` (extend existing tests)

**Call sites to refactor** (approximate line numbers per spec; verify current lines before editing — file has changed since spec was written):
~33, ~48, ~67, ~99, ~127, ~178, ~194, ~229, ~319, ~340, ~360, ~377, ~435, ~455, ~482.

**Session creation flow (`POST /api/sessions`):**
```ts
// 1. Resolve the effective runtime type in priority order.
const runtimeType =
  body.runtime // explicit client hint (future-proof for Codex)
  ?? agentManifest?.runtime // e.g., 'claude-code' | 'codex'
  ?? runtimeRegistry.getDefaultType();

// 2. Persist BEFORE starting the session.
await runtimeRegistry.persistSessionRuntime(sessionId, runtimeType, body.agentPath);

// 3. Resolve for use in this request.
const runtime = await runtimeRegistry.resolveForSession(sessionId);

// 4. Start the session with this runtime.
await runtime.startSession(sessionId, /* ... */);
```

**All other handlers** (list, get, messages, update, approvals, history, tasks, interrupt):
Replace `runtimeRegistry.getDefault()` with `await runtimeRegistry.resolveForSession(sessionId)` where `sessionId` is already available on the request (path param or body). Legacy sessions are transparently inferred and persisted by `resolveForSession`.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] `grep -n "runtimeRegistry.getDefault()" apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts` returns zero hits.
- [ ] Creating a session without hints persists `runtime='claude-code'` (server default).
- [ ] Creating a session with `body.runtime='test-mode'` persists `runtime='test-mode'` and routes to the test-mode runtime on all subsequent requests.
- [ ] Requests against a pre-existing session (no metadata row) succeed and infer-on-access `claude-code`.
- [ ] Existing `routes/sessions.test.ts` scenarios all pass; new test covers explicit `runtime` hint at creation.
- [ ] Request latency impact of per-session DB lookup is <2ms on local dev (informally verified, no benchmark required).

